  "summary": "Frankie experiences a sudden insight regarding the death of Mr. Savage. She theorizes that Basington-French impersonated Savage to sign a will before a lawyer and two witnesses who did not know the real man. Frankie suspects the real Savage was drugged and hidden in an attic for twelve hours, after which he was given triethylamine to ensure he would be found dead the next morning. To prove this, Frankie suggests authenticating the signature or questioning Ross Chaddle (Pratt), though she notes Pratt may have been chosen for her lack of intelligence.\n\nTo further their investigation, Bobby and Frankie seek information on Evans, a former maid at Tudor Cottage. They visit a post office where the postmistress reveals that Evans, formerly Gladys Evans, has married and moved to Wales, where she is now known as Mrs. Roberts. They discover her address is the Parsonage in Machabert, Wales. Realizing they had overlooked this information, they decide to travel home immediately. Frankie provides Bobby with money to settle Baz's debts, suggesting Frankie's father buy Baz's auto repair shop.\n\nDriven by a sense of urgency and a hunch that something is happening, the pair drives to Medshaw Airport. Frankie arranges a plane through Donald Gold to reach their destination quickly. They arrive at the vicarage in Marchbanks as the sun sets. There, they encounter Moira, who appears distressed. Moira confirms she has also figured out the truth regarding Evans, but as Bobby invites her inside, she steps back.",
